The National Rescue Movement on Saturday held her state congress at the party’s secretariat in Birnin Kebbi to prepare for the forthcoming general elections in 2023 in Nigeria. Speaking at the venue of the congress, the state chairman Faruk Garba Nato who retained his seat vie consensus said that, NRM is set to rescue Nigerians from the shackles of hunger, unemployment, general insecurity which has plagued the country since Buhari led APC came on board. According to him, APC deceived Nigerians with fake promises of jobs, fight against corruption but instead, Nigerians are now witnessing the opposite “our roads are no longer safe, one cannot travel from Kaduna to Abuja and from Kebbi to Niger because of insecurity which the president is showing lip services to, even in our houses we are not safe because gunmen pick people from their homes and take them hostage in order to collect a ransom. Speaking further Garba stated that, the time is now to rescue Nigeria through the movements as the two political parties so far have failed Nigerians. The occasion had in attendance INEC officials and delegates from the 21 local governments in Kebbi who vie voice affirmation confirmed the elections of the 21 state executives to stir the party for the period of four years. Delivering his message to the jubilant crowd on behalf of the National headquarters Malam Bashir Altine Mambo said that the National rescue movement remains the envy of other parties in the country because they are poised to change the change” NRM is a poor party for the poor but inside it are dedicated followers who cannot be enticed with monies as their drive for holistic resolve to rescue Nigeria is unshaken, so the ruling APC should be ready to vacate Aso rock in 2023 to give those who will end insecurity and give meaning to the lives of Nigerians who are constantly living in fear since the APC took over he said. Faruk Garba Nato, state chairman, state secretary Nasir Umar and Sahura Muktar vice-chairman were promptly inaugurated by barrister Usman Kaoje who administered the oath to the new excos of the party.